Florencia Carire Tamo, 2 de julio 2010, Trinidad
You came back here, you remembered me again, I thought you forgot me.
Ha vuelto a venir se ha acordado de m otra vez, cre que me haba olvidado.
I moved, now my home is here.
Nuti nejkoripo juiti te pjoka mpeno .
Yo ya me traslad ahora aqu en mi casa
I bought this land and I had this home built, which is mine.
nwachpuekrii pjoka poge ene nemepiareko pjoka mpenorii .
he comprado esta tierra y mand hacer esta que es mi casa.
But you know that as women we are alone, it's hard, isn't it ?
Etotsero pecho piti to viti senono vkejwosjiii kuesta ene ?
Pero usted sabe que nosotras las mujeres somos solas, cuesta no ?
and the man who is my partner now isn't (wasn't ?) here yet, he doesn't (didn't ?) help me yet.
ene ijinaricho i chane nkompaeerii juiti / wicho timkatakanu .
y no hay (habia?) todava el hombre que es mi compaero ahora, todava no me ha (habia?) ayudado.
But um our way of working, as women, our way of working, working hard, thanks to it I managed to build this home, mine.
Enetsero , to manjee ... to vemtonerepiono viti senono vyeerepiono , mraka nkemtone tosooi to nitrukpo pjoka mpeno .
Pero eso s, este nuestra forma de trabajar nosotras las mujeres nuestra forma de trabajar, trabajo duro es por eso que logre conseguir esta mi casa.
And I left my daughter where I lived before (where my home was), in the Machetero street.
Ene esupo su nchicha neraikrii te to mpenoriini kalie Machetero .
Y a mi hija la dej donde era mi casa calle Machetero.
There are a lot of big trees there, mandarin tree, tamarind tree, tamarind, that's what you know Panchita.
Eto movera wkugiono tayee chpegie , eto mandarina , tamarin ... tamarinagi , eto simotgiene esu suka Panchita .
Eso, muchos rboles hay ah grueso, la mandarina, tamarindo, tamarindo, eso es lo que conoce esta Panchita.
And when you were looking for me, my daughter told you : Go to the place called Virgen de Loreto !
Ene te tankompo , sjichpo su nchicha pyonore te to tkjare Virgen de Loreto .
Y cuando me busc, le dijo mi hija: vas a ir donde se llama Virgen de Loreto
That's what she said, she told you "go, go to the beltway".
ene skepo , sjichpo esu pyonyore pion ... piopnoyre te to circunvalacin .
Y as dijo, le dijo ella vas a ir, vas a ir a la circunvalacin.
There, there is this beautiful street um, they already put this, this, the street won't be muddy anymore, in the other language (Spanish) they call it asphalt, they say.
Ene jokrojooi pjokro kaya tyuunapo eto , manjeeripo , nanokripo , eto to ... to tayee ,... to tyraji wipo torajipewyore esu , te to puechjiriiwo ajfaltado nakoe .
All hay esa calle que ya es bonita esta ya este, ya le pusieron, eso, eso, su, el barro ya no tendr su pie ella, en el otro idioma se dice asfaltado, dicen.
And also thanks to God in the sky, um again, what we do (since a while) is always despised by the bad men, our sons who don't understand.
Ene tomuire rusrupaya i tata viya vigienu te anumo , manjeewrepo to vkemtonejira jmaono ... naeprurujiksariono jirono winarajono , wchichanoviono muechemrekono .

Y tambin gracias a Dios nuestro Seor en el cielo, este otra vez, lo que venimos haciendo estos que son siempre despreciados por los hombres malos, y nuestros hijos que no entienden/que no valoran/hacen caso.
And I do again also what I don't know.
Ene nuti nkemtonejiwrepo tomuire eto to mmuitkogne .
Y le hago otra vez tambin lo que no conozco.
And they say "maybe you know Mama" they say to me.
Ene eno nakoe " akaso pitkoriyo meme " najicho .
Y ellos dicen "acaso sabes mam" me dicen.
"Lo que venga" les digo yo (de verdad).
Our Lord, our father, gave to me what I under.. what I am going to understand, what I am currently working on.
Tijroknu ei Viya tkochichawokovi to ... to nechemchog ... to nechemchoyrepo eto to nemtonereprii
Ene jechuraigneei (puis mis dans phrase prcdente) ei i via, to nechemchoreoo, to nemtoneriprii

But this is finished now and they say to me : "are you well paid ?" they say it.
pochpotsero eto , ene najichnu " chopewchovi @", nakoe .
pero ya est terminado eso y me dicen, "te pagan bien?" as dicen.
And I keep quiet because it's my business um, the, the work, because all I want is to learn.
Ene nuti nmotnaaraji tajicho / neerichu manjee nuti , to ... to motneko , ( taejcho ) puejchu nwooo to nitkoyre .

Y yo me callo porque es solo mo este yo, el, el trabajo, porque lo que quiero es aprender.
So I am grateful when it's over, they completed it, they made it like that, the persons in charge made it beautiful.
Entse eto rusrupaya nkepo te to pochpo tamutpo ene tajicho tyuunanaji najicho no techonrii .
Entonces gracias digo cuando termina ya concluye as lo hizo es bonito lo han hecho los responsables.
But after they remembered um of the rainy season.
Ene takeptsero nachopo eto to ... manjee ... to unemuono .
Y pero despus se acordaron este de las pocas de aguas.
And here, when the water goes up, it get us to go out (of the houses), we are leaving our land like earthworms.
Ene to tyopno to une te pjoka oni asike tve... tkuchrukovi viuchrurupueko wkuti to chepi .
Y cuando sube el agua aqu, as es que nos hace salir, salimos como las lombrices.
We go away, we pile up in um... height.
Vyompo viuumuttujpo te to ... manjee ... nugipai .
Nos vamos nos amontonamos en este la altura.

And she said, the... "last year, I didn't know there was going to be these houses".
Ene skepo esu su " ponapo ao , eto wo necharii nuti to etjooirayore jmani petyono ".

Y dijo ella, la "el otro ao, eso yo no saba que haban estas casas".
I knew that they were going to build these houses only in Pedro Ignacio Muiba.
Nechorii nuti techujcha te to Peru nasio Muiwa to nanosoyre eto jmani petyono .
Saba yo que solo en Pedro Ignacio Muiba que iban a hacer estas casas.
The house is three meters height.
nuge mopona metro to tangiewo to peti .
Alta tres metros es la altura de la casa.
And I didn't suppose, I didn't say, "make the same for my home", I didn't say it.
Ene nuti wo ... wo nechkapo , wo nake nuti , " epiasnanu to mpenoyore " wo nake .
Y yo no supuse, no dije yo, "hganme para mi casa" no dije.
I went to work in another small ranch.
Nompo nkemtone te to pona ranchogra .
Fui a trabajar a otro ranchito.
There, they called me, them, them, the persons in charge.
nogi timichoriknompo eno ... eno no techonrii :
All me hicieron llamar ellos, ellos, los responsables:
"the foreign woman of the bank, she came back"
" tchoopo esu su pona wrinka financiera ."
And she told me "you are going to have a surprise", she said.
Ene tmetokompo " jokro pyee sorpresa " skoe .
Y me dijo "vas a tener una sorpresa" dijo.
I didn't know what it was.
In fact, she called me and she asked me if... if I already finished paying the land.
Jechuraigneei esu tmetokompo ene tyoseriknutsero to ni nitopopka to nwacho to poge .
Verdaderamente ella me avis y pero me pregunt que si si ya termin de pagar la tierra.
And I told her, "I already finished paying it but I don't have the documents yet".
Ene njichpo " nuti nitoripo nwacho etotsero tajinaricho to ... to tayeeyore jiumruko ".
Y le dije "yo ya termin de pagar pero no tengo todava los papeles".
"Show me this, your payment (receipt)" said the woman in charge, and I showed it to her.
" Pimechanu eto to tawacho " skepo esu su techo , ene time ... nimechpo .
"Mostrame, eso, su pago" dijo ella la encargada, y le mostr.
Then um they built, they assured me that the big house, the beautiful house, was going to be built.
Tosooi to ... manjeepo ... naemepiarekpo to ... nkijarepo nomuire to tkepiayreei eto chope peti , tyuuna peti .

And now um... women have it (the house) as a reference.
Ene eto juiti to manjee ... nakimotyora eno chaono vennoviono .
Y eso ahora este... la tienen como referencia las seoras.
Y eso ahora este... la tienen como referencia las gentes, seoras.
